Beta

Daniel Suh

28 February, 2023

library(here)

source(here("base","src.R"))
beta.summary <- readRDS(here("processed_data", "beta_summary.rds"))

Beta was estimated by bootstrapping 95% confidence intervals around a mean using data on probability of infection, exposure dose, exposure time, and exposure volume.

beta.summary %>% filter(species=="D" & temp %in% const_temp) %>% ggplot(.,aes(x=trt, y = beta.est, color = temp)) +
  geom_point(aes(), position = position_dodge(width = 0.5)) + 
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = beta.025, ymax = beta.975), position = position_dodge(width = 0.5)) +
  theme_minimal() + labs(y = "Beta", x = "ID", title = "Beta: Transmission Parameter")

Exposure dose, time, and volume were meant to be consistent across all treatments which means that Beta should end up as a function of the probability of infection. As expected, the patterns in Beta and probabilities of infection match well.

prevalence <- readRDS(here("processed_data", "prevalence.rds"))
